{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"137b98bc-676c-4812-83ac-01261c22319c","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter entirely.** It ships only with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP), so `vstest.console` can't discover tests — there's no adapter for it to load.\n\n### Your options\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended)\n`dotnet test` works with MTP out-of-the-box (requires .NET SDK ≥ 9.0.200, or set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`).\n\n**Option B — Re-enable the VSTest bridge**\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nThis adds a compatibility layer so `vstest.console` can still discover and run tests through MTP.\n\n**Option C — Pin to 3.x until you're ready to migrate**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n```\n\nOption A is the cleanest long-term path — it avoids the overhead of the bridge layer entirely.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f82b1fd-bb80-4165-be9a-0d7b3d63831e","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"340A:104E71:10E232:149F87:69F416C3"},"id":"40da2f9d-86bb-4b40-9709-4abc4bc59474","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:58:18.025Z","parentId":"7058433a-c77c-48ac-b1d1-a491425368a5"}
